    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Legendary creatures having the head, trunk, and arms of a man joined to the body and legs of a horse. The term derives from early Greek literature where it referred to a savage tribe of Thessaly, who were said to be expert horse riders.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
